# Frontend code quality (ESLint + Next)

CI runs `npm run lint` then `npm run build` on PRs. Fix lint locally first.

## Commands

| Command | Use |
|---------|-----|
| `npm run lint` | ESLint (same as CI) |
| `npm run lint:fix` | Auto-fix what ESLint can |
| `npm run check` | Lint + production build (closest to full gate) |

## Conventions

- Follow **eslint-config-next** / core-web-vitals rules.
- Prefer explicit types over `any`; handle `catch` errors properly.
- Remove unused imports/vars or prefix with `_` if intentional.
- Run `npm run lint:fix` after bulk edits, then fix remaining issues by hand.

Before opening a PR: `npm run check` (or at least `npm run lint`).
